The paper deals with establishing dense correspondences between two images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper specifically addresses the challenge of local scale differences between objects in the two images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions interest points, which are commonly used in computer graphics and image processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also mentions using image information to guide scale propagation, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper's approach involves exploiting context, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
